<br>
It has been recommend to me that a new rank structure should be put in place based at least partly on realm points, thus the proposed ranks and requirement as listed below.<br>
<br>
Note that although rank 3 is listed as Battle Commander, any member of the High Council or a Steward or the Chief can be a Battle Commander. The rank of Jarlar is for one who does not wish to participate in the civil governance of the Siol but has been designated as a leader in war. Likewise, when the commander has been selected by the Chief or highest ranking member of the Siol present, ALL, including the Chief will follow his or her lead and commands until that campaign is completed or he or she is replaced by proper authority!<br>
<br>
0 = Chief  - Laird of the Siol<br>
     everything enabled<br>
1 = Steward - Authorized to act in the name of the Laird<br>
     everything enabled <br>
2 = High Council - Advisors to the Chief and Laird, authorized to act on his orders<br>
     evrything enabled<br>
3 = Jarlar - Battle Commanders<br>
     Alliance and Officer speak enabled<br>
4 = Hersar - 20,000+ realm points<br>
5 = Boenor - 10,000+ realm points<br>
6 = Holdar - 5,000+ realm points<br>
7 = Praelar - 1,000+ realm points<br>
8 = Kin - One proven to be worthy of membership in the family of Lear across all worlds and lands. Nominated by at least two who are already Kin and attested to by an officer of the Siol (Jarlar and above). All ranks above kin are by definition, Kin. Thus, one who joins us with many realm points and is authorized Kinship may immediately rise to a higher rank. <br>
9 = Applicant - One who has requested to join the Siol and is on probation until he or she has proven worthy of the name.<br>
<br>
I recognize we have dropped the concept of Lad/Lass, but it seems to have outlived its usefullness at this point. If one is above applicant, one can wear the sigil at the 20th season and represents us to the world. If one is worthy to bear the name and sigil he or she should be worthy to be one of us.<br>
<br>
Your comments are solicited <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/upeldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peldor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steward</span><br>  Posts: 541<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/26/01 6:55:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I like the structure and think we should have a meeting on an upcoming weekend night when all can be there. Perhaps this coming Sunday or the week after? <br>
