 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulegarmaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legar MacLear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 1:37:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: raises a few questions</span><hr size=1> When you say the rank of applicant seems to mean they haven't been accepted yet, you are right. We are a family, and until one is deemed worthy of the name Siol Lear, a sort of probation period is required. This isn't meant to look down on someone, but to give them and us both time to see if the fit is there. Perhaps applicant is not the best sounding word, but it means exactly what it says. <br>
<br>
The answer to the Kin question is right there in Loden's post. To become Kin one needs the recommendation of two folks that are kin already or someone of High Council status or above to approve. <br>
<br>
I can't always drop what I'm doing and run somewhere to promote someone to Kin, but I've tried to do my best. I normally speak to the person and work out a time or place that we can meet. I wholeheartedly agree we should have more meetings and this being one of the big reasons. I agree that folks are reluctant to ask when they're ok'd to become Kin. It's awkward I think. A meeting every two to three weeks would help eliminate officers from running around (although I think this should go with the territory of being an officer. It is our job to get out and meet the new folk more than it is thier job to come to us.) and it would also allow the newer people to meet the others in the guild. If Loden cannot hold meetings like this due to personal time constraints, perhaps I can do it for him and get the newer folk together with others that are online, with the major guild meetings being conducted by Loden. Think this a good idea??<br>
<br>
As for the last question...In my opinion (it's ultimately up to Loden) noone starts off automatically as Kin. See my first paragraph for the reasons why. The only exceptions that I've seen made are for the folks from EQ that were already a part of MacLear. Either as a member of Clan MacLear or the great ally Crusaders of the High Plains. <br>
<br>
If anyone has questions on who in Siol Lear is an officer, go to the roster page. The Stewards and High Council members are listed there. <br>
<br>
Hope this clears some things up. I've kinda dropped the ball a bit on getting out there and meeting the newer folks, will try to pick that up a bit from now on. <br>
