Cali lvl 37 healer<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utorgeirr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torgeirr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 6:34:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I think &quot;applicant&quot; is a reasonable term for the 9th rank, since its not meant to be something that is long term.  As has been pointed out, folks are often slow about asking for promotion out of &quot;applicant&quot;.  I think in large part its because the process for advancing beyond that rank has not been made clear.  We should post a good description of what is needed both off the home page, and again directly on the application form.  Getting rid of lad/lass rank might help to clear the confusion.  While I don't mind the concept of a rank in between applicant and kin, the fact that the current lad/lass can't wear the emblem makes it in my opinion a bad idea, so I'm just as happy to see it go.<br>
<br>
Having meetings every 2-3 weeks might or might not work.  We can try it and see. I suspect people will get &quot;meeting'ed out&quot; after the 2nd one. More importantly, though, I think needing to wait for a guild meeting to be promoted would tend to slow things down, which is bad.  Yes, the meetings can provide an opportunity of last resort if you can't catch an officer earlier, but we can often get to people within a day or two at most -- and typically we've been getting them the same day --once we are alerted to the fact that someone needs to be promoted.  In practice its been learning of the need that takes the time, not doing the deed.  Especially if the candidate is willing to travel to an officer.<br>
<br>
As for the actual proposal, here are a few issues to consider.<br>
<br>
* The majority of guild members would need to be re-ranked. In particular, most folks who are Kin, Noble, Black Watch, or Captain of the Black Watch would need to be re-ranked by hand.<br>
<br>
* I think the names are a bad idea.  The names should be ones that have some intrinsic meaning to most of the members of the guild, not something understood by only a few people.<br>
<br>
* There's more RvR ranks proposed here than we really need, and the point values don't fit well with the game. I agree that 1000 points is a good starting point since it requires a little, but not a lot, of effort. The game gives Rank 2 at 7200 points, which is not that much different than the value of 5000 in the proposal. In game terms, RvR Rank 3 is at 62,500 points (I think). If we used that for our ranking, it certainly would indicate quite a step up in effort, which makes it a meaningful distinction. With the current breakpoints at 1K, 5K, 10K, and 20K, there's not that much difference of effort between the 2nd and 3rd, and even less (in actual practice even if the absolute number appears on the suface to be great) between the 3rd and 4th. Once you have the hang of RvR to the extent that you can get 5K points, going up to 20K isn't that big a hurdle -- which is why Mythic set the marks where they did. Relating guild ranks to the game ranks for the 2nd and 3rd levels also has the advantage of being confirmable once Mythic implements titles.<br>
<br>
Based on these observations, I suggest that we have an RvR rank at 1000 points, another at the game's R2 value (7200 points) and a third at the games R3 value (I think 62,500 points).  If you really think we need 4 RvR ranks, then insert one between 7200 and 62,500, perhaps at 30,000.  That will be a much more in tune with the true amount of effort required to get from one step to the next, and give more staying power if we plan to be playing this game for more than a month or two yet.<br>
<br>
* The proposal only addresses the issue of ranks.  There's been a lot of discussion about battle groups but not so much done, and a lot of confusion about what &quot;Black Watch&quot; is supposed to mean.  We should deal with both the issue of ranks and the issue of battle groups at the same time.<br>
<br>
Does this proposal mean that we are doing away completely with the Black Watch?  I understand that Legar is creating a new battle group.  Some of us have tentatively formed a battle group named the Jomsvikings.  But we didn't say much about it and let it hang because it wasn't clear what the guild wanted to do with battle group organization.  Does this proposal mean that we should be moving ahead on this?<br>
       -- Gisli<br>
