*grin* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 6:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I personally think that RP are their own reward ( or at least will be in the future).  Will Tradecrafters have an alternate point set up to fall within ranks, or will they just be thier own thing?  Also, RP are harder to get for some classes than others, and rank x will really have a different meaning for some classes than for others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utabot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 6:45:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> Good point Onahoo! Tradeskillers usually don't get out much, and it takes at least as much commitment as it does to attain RvR Ranks... and they normally benefit the guild as a whole with their gear-making abilities. <p>Ohlar, Skald of Siol Lear<BR>Harl, Runemaster and Tailor of Siol Lear</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utabot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/27/01 6:46:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utorgeirr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torgeirr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 7:14:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> Good point about tradecrafters!  I think that a trade-skill person who has reached the appropriate level and who participates in RvR by making seigecraft should get promoted to the RvR ranks in some way parallel to obtaining realm points.  For example:<br>
<br>
After the first time you actively participate in creating a siege craft item used in a keep raid you get the first RvR rank.<br>
<br>
After some other objective mark has been reached (maybe 3 sieges with at least one successful, plus at least one significant door repair) you reach the 2nd RvR rank.<br>
<br>
And so on.<br>
        -- Gisli<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 10:54:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure why you ran with tradeskills !=siegecrafting, but anyone can pick up siegecrafting.<br>
<br>
Not only that, but it would be sort of silly to pick up siegecrafting as an armorcrafter or leathercrafter, since siege is capped at 40% of main skill, so the current best you could get is around 350 siege, and the best (after the level 40-49 materials) ever would be around 460 seige, where an weaponscrafter or fletcher could do almost double that.<br>
<br>
Any guild supporting a siegecrafter would be silly to use an armor or leathercrafter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulodenmaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loden MacLear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chief of Siol Lear</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/27/01 11:32:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I hear you. Now that I think about it, the RvR ranking system in-game provides a clear way to set up the guild ranks. It even has names although I have no idea what they are. If someone will give me the names that characters get at levels one, two, and three I will be glad to change the names to those. I agree that 1000, 7200 and 62500 would be good rank levels.<br>
<br>
-Now that we have the guild ranks earned by RvR down to three, what do we do with the other rank? Do we want to insert one at 30000?<br>
<br>
-By the way, the ranks I set up were taken from Norse class ranking in the time of the Vikings. The Jarlar was a battle chieftain, Hersar was a sub-Chief, Boenor was a master over a area of land, Holdar was a holder of land and a Praelar was a person who was eligible for holding land.<br>
<br>
-I think it would be good to have a monthly meeting. I am open to any specific time, but probably something like the first Sunday evening of a month at a specific time and place would be good... Comments?<br>
<br>
-As to promotion to Kin... I think, given the busyness of our schedules and gaming time, it would be good for those wanting to be kin to request a promotion. I know that is a bit of a pain, but keeping up with who is what is a massive task as there is no way I can call up a name and know the owners rank! I would LOVE to have that ability in-game and have asked for it in apppeal, but as they have not done it, I suppose I am the only one doing so to date. If the person wishing to be promoted would contact one of the senior officers and let us know who they have been with recently so we can request endorsement it would be helpful. I, for one, dont mind a few tells as long as the teller can wait until I dispatch or am dispatched by what or whomever I am fighting! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulegarmaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legar MacLear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/28/01 11:34:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> &quot;* I think the names are a bad idea. The names should be ones that have some intrinsic meaning to most of the members of the guild, not something understood by only a few people.&quot;<br>
<br>
Loden explained the meaning to the names of the ranks in his suggestion. Good enough for me, I like the names and appreciate Loden taking the time to look them up. <br>
<br>
&quot;* The proposal only addresses the issue of ranks. There's been a lot of discussion about battle groups but not so much done, and a lot of confusion about what &quot;Black Watch&quot; is supposed to mean. We should deal with both the issue of ranks and the issue of battle groups at the same time.<br>
<br>
Does this proposal mean that we are doing away completely with the Black Watch? I understand that Legar is creating a new battle group. Some of us have tentatively formed a battle group named the Jomsvikings. But we didn't say much about it and let it hang because it wasn't clear what the guild wanted to do with battle group organization. Does this proposal mean that we should be moving ahead on this?&quot;<br>
<br>
The Black Watch was formed as the bodyguard to our Laird and Chief in lands long lost. It was carried forward to Midgard and a select few were chosen by the Captain. It was asked by Torveig for it not to be a guild rank, that it just be a team. Now that Torveig does not have time to lead a team around, there is no longer a Black Watch. I have contacted 15 folks about starting our own team. (just hadn't made that public yet, thanks Gisli <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) I'm in hopes that Gisli and others form teams as well. I plan on practicing RvR with the team I've made, and working hand in hand with any other groups formed. There will be no rank given to the teams in the guild structure. It's not needed.<br>
<br>
Nothing is final here folks, the headline to this thread reads PROPOSED. The numbers separating the ranks were just used as an example, not knowing what the in game ones were. <br>
<br>
As far as tradeskills go....This proposed rank system is based on the majority of folks wishing some recognition for RvR accomplishments. The proposed RvR ranks are totally separate from the guild governing ranks. If someone is the highest rank on the RvR ladder, he's still Kin. If someone is sitting in front of the forge with a skill in the 800's, he's still Kin. We're family, not one single brother or sister is more important than another. That's how I view it anyway. <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Legar MacLear <br>
Steward of Siol Lear <br>
Troll Shaman</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=abbatoir>Abbatoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/28/01 2:20:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> *-By the way, the ranks I set up were taken from Norse class ranking in the time of the Vikings. The Jarlar was a battle chieftain, Hersar was a sub-Chief, Boenor was a master over a area of land, Holdar was a holder of land and a Praelar was a person who was eligible for holding land.*<br>
<br>
Though these names at first were a bit unintuitive to me too, seeing what they do indeed mean actually makes me feel 'stoked' to use them! Tapadh leigh, Laird Loden, ye 'ave captured the heart of this Mitgaard defender. <br>
<br>
I actually see that the top 3 as the actual Guild Ranks. The bottom 3 - From being eligible to hold, to being recognized as a holder of land, to being a master of an area of land, are three very viable ranks of our RvR active Kin - but do not neccesarily have to be Ingame Guild rankings... At the moment, ranks are not visible, once they are then whether someone is tier 4 kin or not will need to be worked out. <br>
<br>
For now - a web based ranking would actually serve the Reward and Recognition better then the ingame set up [as all 4 kins slots do not really have any different permissions unless I am wrong?] RvR groups will need their OWN internal ranking structures, which at the moment may be better kept web-based?<br>
<br>
Perhaps Praeler to Boenor should then be Guild Site based definitions and rewards of our RvR active Kin is what I am saying <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They have the same abilities and permissions, and ye may wish to reserve Rank slots for other folks that need the different chat-channels ranking set up confers [especially once alliance agendas become paramount] - if ye were to make any particular RP number conducive to attaining an ingame Ranking, as Torg pointed out getting 5000 after 1000 is not such a leap - so why not just make getting 5000 the point when ye attain this recognition of being Praelar [or Defender which encompasses Praeler to Boenor]. Just an idea <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Siol Lear itself should be seen more as a High Court for the sub-groups - to which the sub-groups pledge fealty. Siol Lear empowers them by conferring the channels of communication needed to empower the Leaders, and those that rally under the different banners. In exchange.. the Realm Points reflect collectively under the Mother Guild of Siol Lear, bringing her to Glory.<br>
<br>
In all - I think that our rank definitions will continue to grow as our own agendas change, the game is evolving, so I am happy to see our own ranks adapting with the tide. In times to come - we may see some folks get together just to make a band of ShadowBlades for deep frontier activities.. initiatives such as these may come and go.. possibly may actually figure out a way to have 'temporary folks fighting under siol lears banner' to rack up more RP a minute then a family set up allows.. lol - i am not advocating this, am just saying that agendas do change as the game does.. so changes like I am seeing proposed here really do give me confidence in the future of our Guild.<br>
<br>
Thankee!<br>
 - Abbatoir <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=abbatoir>Abbatoir</A> at: 12/28/01 2:53:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jenguss>Jenguss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/28/01 3:35:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> This all seems to be working out nicely but I would like to voice one or two of my concerns by what I am seeing. I think that a meeting once a month is a grand idea and if you keep them short and sweet no one should be bored by them and it is a good way to adventure out afterwards. As in RL people will tend to gravitate to certain others all the time which is how we form bonds, however this also will tend to leave others out of the circles. I understand that this game really dose not go well with people of lower levels grouping with those of higher but I think this is mainly for fighting the game characters and not for RVR, correct me if I am wrong. My point is the newer people will most likely get stuck having to group with others outside of the Siol if there are already formed groups. The best way to learn RVR is with people who already know the ins and outs of it and most people would feel more comfortable doing this inside of the family. I am not saying this is or would happen but I can see the begging of this starting to form. Just my two cents worth take as much of it as you want. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulegarmaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legar MacLear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/28/01 3:47:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> Jenguss, I'm not forming a group of Lears to make a clique. When there are guild functions, we will not be in our groups, we will be with our entire family. Groups will be set up as the raid leader sees fit, not by what team you belong to.<br>
<br>
Even when it's not a guild raid, there will be many times when not everyone is available to be online. At those times, spots in the groups will be opened and filled by those needing groups that want to RvR with us. <br>
<br>
Lower levels in high level groups are ok, but the enemy goes after the ones that con lower to them all the time. Constantly forcing your group to try and rescue you from dead. Can be trouble, but something I'm willing to deal with if someone wants to come along to see the frontiers and RvR. <br>
<br>
 <p>Legar MacLear <br>
Steward of Siol Lear <br>
Troll Shaman</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=193.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=193.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=193.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.threadControl?topicID=193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=193.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=193.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub5.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="theclanmacleargeneral">The Great Hall<option value="theclanmaclearfrm8">Inner Court<option value="theclanmaclearfrm6">Events<option value="theclanmaclearfrm5">Pro